cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for sentence compression. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses a denoising auto-encoder, which is a type of neural network, indicating that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves unsupervised learning, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of auto-encoders also suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves text summarization, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it involves processing and understanding textual data.
